  "instructions": [
    "Heat olive oil in a Dutch oven over medium heat.",
    "Add diced onion, carrot, and celery and sauté until softened, about five minutes.",
    "Stir in minced garlic and cook for one minute until fragrant.",
    "Mix in tomato paste, dried thyme, rosemary, and cracked pepper, cooking for two minutes.",
    "Add rinsed lentils, vegetable stock, and shio-koji, bring to a simmer.",
    "Reduce heat, cover, and let cook for twenty-five minutes until lentils are tender and broth thickened.",
    "Stir in truffle oil and adjust seasoning with salt if needed.",
